reviews.review_text: Been coming to the clinic since 2008 after my car accident. I now live in Nanaimo and still use the Commercial Drive Clinic. They re always helpful with everything I need done from so far. Thanks for your help over the years. I appreciate it.
Thank you guys so much! Getting in to see a doctor can be super tough lately because of covid. However, they were able to get me in right away to take care of me :) Nice staff, thanks everyone there

Booking my first appointment wasn t particularly easy as there is no booking confirmation and my appointment had to be moved and there was confusion between the staff - as I m sure happens with a booking system that s not super intuitive. However I did get a call the morning of my appointment to check I was coming in and the staff were friendly. I had a really good experience with Dr Mark Abbey, as a foreigner in Vancouver without my own Dr here it s always hit and miss with a walk in clinic. I found Dr Abbey was friendly and actually listened to why I was there rather than pushing me out the door moments after arriving which is how I feel most of the time seeing Drs in this city. It was nice to feel like a person not a number (:
reviews.response_from_owner_text: We are grateful for your fabulous review of our walk-in medical clinic. All of our staff, from the receptionist, nurses, doctors, and physicians are here to ensure your well being and safety. reviews.review_text: One of THE best clinics Ive been to. I never write reviews on Google and this is my first one, but this clinic deserves acknowledgment for their sincere and great work! reviews.review_text: Probably the best clinic on the drive. Ive been going here for all my problems for the past several months and havent had any problems. They always answer the phones, they take walk ins on short notice (they dont close right when they open like other clinics on the drive), and the bedside manner is impeccable. Most other doctors make me feel rushed and I feel that the doctors here take the most time that they can with their patients, which seems to be a rarity here in Vancouver. The clinic is small but well kept and is relatively accessible from commercial-Broadway skytrain.

reviews.review_text: Walked in to this clinic several months ago after seeing a doctor elsewhere (that told me I had a bad cold and prescribed me cough syrup with codeine). I was sick for weeks and couldnt breathe and was staying up all night with a rattle in my chest. Walked in to this clinic, was seen right away with no wait time at all, and explained my situation to the doctor. She didnt say much, which at first I thought was off-putting, but I quickly realised she was doing her job properly and professionally. She assessed me, told me I had bronchitis and that I had gotten much worse since the other Dr. at another clinic had misdiagnosed my symptoms. She quickly prescribed me some antibiotics and an inhaler to help clear my chest. I felt better within a couple of days. If not for her I fear I may have gotten much worse. 10/10 would recommend this clinic, as the staff are competent and understanding. They arent customer service representatives, they are health-care professionals, and thats what I want when I see a doctor.

Dr Gillian Fisher and receptionist Nina are brusque, highly competent, kind, overworked, helpful, and professional. If Dr Fisher had her own practice, Id have her as my own doctor in a heartbeat. Dr Roger Dickey and other doctors Ive seen here have also been great. The wait gets longer as the day progresses, and sometimes the last hour or two are already full by mid-afternoon, just like all walk-in clinics in the neighbourhood. I recommend going as early as you can, or plan to go to the park or do errands nearby.
Dr Amir is by far the best doctor Ive ever went too, hes knowledgeable & fast and helpful. The receptionist are amazing too!

I love this walk-in clinic. Ive never had to wait. The doctors aways listen to me. I dont understand why its rated so low. I always come here when my family doctor is too busy and booked far in advance. IF I could get my family doctor here, I would! Seriously, check it out!

Doctor was amazing. There was a long wait, but that depends on when you go and how busy it is. It is after all a walk in clinic. And the doctor spent a full 25 minutes with me because I was a complicated case. And I appreciated what she did, I walked out with much fewer worries , and she made sure I got the tests I needed. They even called me for a follow up the next day.
I find it odd that a lot of low reviews.  Every time I come here, everyone is very attentive and approachable. The doctors and receptionist are concise and friendly. I recommend this place.

reviews.review_text: Made an appointment 3 weeks ago online. Never received a confirmation or a phone call to confirm, so I took it upon myself to do that. reviews.review_text: This office is so disrespectful they told me a doctor would call me and it s been two days they have not called me. They need to find a new solution where they can accommodate everybody s needs. I m very unhappy and disappointed at this.

Terrible experience. I walked in with a requisition. All I needed was a self-administered swab tube.  Receptionist said they couldn t fit me in with a doctor. I don t need a doctor, I repeated several times. I just needed a tube for a self-administered test. They said I needed a requisition. I already have a requisition. They take it, grab a tube for me. Tell me I can t use their bathroom to do the self test, I would have to go somewhere else. I literally walk to the walk-in clinic next door who were more than happy to let me use their washroom to complete the test. I go to drop off the tube at LifeLabs, only to find they have given me the wrong tube. Great. EDIT: In response to the reply - new and training is one thing, but this receptionist was dismissive and patronizing. I had a simple request, and she made the interaction frustrating and I left in disbelief, unsure of what I had done to make her so angry with me.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Dear Chelsey, Thank you for taking the time to leave your concerns. We apologies that you had a bad experience here. Both of our staff are new and they are on training, we will do our best to speed them up. We have tried to contact you multiple time regarding this issue.

reviews.review_text: I called in this morning to make an appointment for a botox consultation and the receptionist told me I had to come in right at that moment as there is no one waiting and they dont do appointments. Given that I work about 10 mins away, I arrived approx 20 mins after the phone call and had to wait another  8-10 mins while the receptionist was on the phone with no acknowledgement. After she took my ID and set me up, I asked  her how long it will take for someone to meet me and she tells me that the doctor has gone on break and wont be back for another at least 30 mins and that there is someone else in front of me. I have no issue waiting my turn and am not upset by this at all. That was completely fair, I saw the women ahead of me waiting before I got there. When I tell the receptionist that I was under the impression there was no wait given what she had told me on the phone, she told me that since the doctor saw no one was there, he went on break. I am not saying that the doctor does not deserve a break but at least schedule the breaks or close the clinic for the 30 mins - 1 hour that break takes place. I have seen many clinics use this method and it works best. My issue is not with the doctor but the incompetent receptionist, given my friends experience, I will come by again for a consultation and we will see if this is an overall staff problem.

reviews.review_text: I originally came here because they update their times on medimap and I saw that they consistently had short wait times. I loved the doctor I saw the first time, and have been back twice since. However, the receptionist ruins the experience and the way that the clinic runs makes it impossible to give this place a good rating. Their times listed are absolutely inaccurate. For example I was there today at 8:50am expecting the clinic to open at 9am. On the door they have no times posted, only online. The clinic finally opened at 9:30am. I walked in and the receptionist said they were not open for walk-ins as no doctors would be in today. I asked why that was not at least posted on the door, she replied theres nothing I can do. I told her that she could post something, even a piece of paper on the door with that information, or update their voicemail (of which they have none) Well at this point Ive taken the day off work, I still need to see a doctor, and all of the clinics are at least an hour wait time. I highly recommend staying away from this place.

Not what you would expect from a doctor, I was 3 times to this place and all of the there times was a complete disappointment. They did not bother explaining what should be done, they never ordered the important analysis that should be done until I went back there and further more when the analysis came back they never bothered to call and when I went there the doctor spent 1 min to give me the result with absolutely zero explanation except, you are good, you need some Vitamin D. WOW I went to the pharmacist next door to get the vitamins and the pharmacist explained 1000% better than this doctor. I felt much more comfortable talking g to the pharmacist than this doctors. If you have choice and if you are there for important reason other than mild headaches or something not very serious than please please find somewhere else. they are a joke
